      • getRegexInput

        private java.lang.String getRegexInput(JCas jcas,
                             SideEffectAnnotator.PotentialSideEffect pse)
        Return a string to be used for regular expression pattern matching Replace a target sign/symptom or disorder/diseas with <@PSE>, a target drug with <@DRUG>, and the other pse and drug with and respectively, and lower cased the rest text. eg) target PSE: upset stomach, target drug: Aspirin Aspirin and Tylenol cause upset stomach -> <@DRUG> and cause <@PSE>
        Parameters:
        jcas -
        pse - instance of PotentialSideEffect
        Returns:
        string that is used for regular expression matching
